1. Quadratic action in momentum space, basis (φ(p),F*(p)) with conjugates (φ*(−p),F(−p)):
$$
S_{\rm quad}
=\int\!dp\;
\bigl(\phi^*(−p),\,F(−p)\bigr)
\begin{pmatrix}p^2 & m\\m & 1\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}\phi(p)\\F^*(p)\end{pmatrix}.
$$
2. Define the kinetic matrix 
$$
M=\begin{pmatrix}a & b\\ b & c\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}p^2 & m\\ m & 1\end{pmatrix}.
$$
3. Its inverse is
$$
M^{-1}
=\frac1{ac-b^2}
\begin{pmatrix}c & -b\\ -b & a\end{pmatrix}
=\frac1{p^2- m^2}
\begin{pmatrix}1 & -m\\ -m & p^2\end{pmatrix}.
$$
4. The propagator matrix is $i\,\Delta(p)=i\,M^{-1}$.
